## Part 4: Big Picture Review (1 hour)

### 4.1 Data Flow

```
Request comes in
    ↓
Middleware chain:
  - RecoveryMiddleware (handles panics)
  - RequestIDMiddleware (adds request ID)
  - LoggingMiddleware (logs request)
  - AuthMiddleware (verifies JWT)
    ↓
Hits router
    ↓
Handler function
  - Extracts parameters
  - Calls business logic
    ↓
Business Logic
  - Validates data
  - Calls repository
    ↓
Data Layer (Repository)
  - Queries database with tenant_id
    ↓
Database returns result
    ↓
Response flows back up through middleware
    ↓
Client gets JSON response
```

### 4.2 Configuration Flow

```
Environment Variables
    ↓
config.LoadConfig()
    ↓
Config struct
    ↓
Passed to:
  - Providers (database, auth)
  - Modules (user, auth)
  - Handlers
  - Logger
```

### 4.3 Module Isolation

Each module:
- Has its own package (`module/X/`)
- Defines its own types
- Implements three layers (DL, BL, HTTP)
- Depends on providers and logger (not other modules)
- Registers routes in main.go

